  "markdown": "[![evolutionQ](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/63ed3a30ffdcab681511d581_evolutionQ_logo.svg)](https://www.evolutionq.com/)\nProducts\n[ BasejumpSKI Symmetric key infrastructure solution that provides long-term security ](https://www.evolutionq.com/products/basejumpski)[ BasejumpQDN Ultra-secure key exchange for evolving quantum networks ](https://www.evolutionq.com/products/basejumpqdn)\nServices\n[ Quantum Risk Assessment Quantum-safe analysis for your risk management program ](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-risk-assessment)[ Quantum Briefing - Executive Workshop Executive briefing on quantum computing and threats by world-renowned experts ](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-safe-executive-workshop)[ Quantum Roadmap & Strategy Building a plan to address the quantum computing threat ](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-roadmap-strategy)\nResources\n[Resources](https://www.evolutionq.com/resources/resources)[Publications](https://www.evolutionq.com/resources/quantum-safe-publications)[FAQ](https://www.evolutionq.com/quantum-safe-cyber-security-faq)\nCompany\n[About](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/about)[Careers](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/quantum-safe-careers)[Events](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/events)[News](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/news)[Partner Program](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/partner-program)[Contact](https://www.evolutionq.com/contact)\n[Blog](https://www.evolutionq.com/blog)\n[evolutionQ Europe](https://evolutionq.eu/)[Contact Us](https://www.evolutionq.com/contact)\n#  Quantum-Safe Executive Workshops\nExecutive briefing on quantum computing threats by world-renowned experts.\n[Get Price](https://frequency.evolutionq.com/get-quote)\n![Quantum-Safe Executive Workshop is pivotal for understanding the risks posed by quantum computing](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/63fbf9c00f51e2025311df82_Quantum-Safe-Executive-Workshop.webp)\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/64374b7d14ce9237281f9f37_quantum.svg)\n##### What is the quantum threat and why act now?\nWhile the technology race has started to find useful and practical applications for quantum computing, in contrast there is a growing concern about the risk posed by quantum computing to cybersecurity and the potential for fraud and business instability.\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/64374b7d5e1ec578430620ec_migration.svg)\n##### High-level risk mitigation and planning\nIdentify the specific systems and data that are most vulnerable to quantum threats, prioritize efforts to enhance cybersecurity measures, and develop a plan to protect against future quantum attacks.\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/64374b7d207c4ef9b61b648f_migrations.svg)\n##### How to organize cryptographic inventories and plan migrations\nNew post-quantum cryptography standards are expected to soon be released and the next large scale cybersecurity migration will soon start. Explore methods and techniques for finding and fixing legacy cybersecurity systems that are vulnerable to quantum threats.\n![Quantum computing](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/64402b9eace1b2fb2b936163_Quantum-computing.webp)\n### Quantum Computing Threats - Separating Facts from Fiction \nQuantum computing is a prevalent topic within technology news that is gaining momentum and critical mass. Often technology leaders find it difficult separate fact from fiction, but still need to answer questions from their C-level executive suite with regards to the impact on the business at large.\n###  Sample agenda - executive briefing tailored for your business leaders\nevolutionQ will tailor executive briefings for your leadership team. Some popular topics that we are frequently asked to cover include:\n  1. Rationale as to what the quantum threat is and why act now.\n  2. Interactive discussions of current high-level risk mitigation and migration planning.\n  3. Guidance on how to organize and execute inventories of cryptography assets across infrastructure, systems and applications.\n  4. Data points to collect over time to help prioritize immediate concerns over long-term nice-to-haves.\n  5. Guidance on approaches to vendor discussions. \n\n\n![](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/643f5f2fda83843e7ee7afff_executive-briefing.webp)\n### Book your tailored workshop today\n[Get Price](https://frequency.evolutionq.com/get-quote)\n[![evolutionQ](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/63ed3a30ffdcab681511d581_evolutionQ_logo.svg)](https://www.evolutionq.com/old-home)\nPRODUCTS\n[BasejumpQDN](https://www.evolutionq.com/products/basejumpqdn)[BasejumpSKI](https://www.evolutionq.com/products/basejumpski)[Technical Support](https://frequency.evolutionq.com/support-login)\nSERVICES\n[Quantum Risk Assessment](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-risk-assessment)[Quantum-Safe Executive Workshop](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-safe-executive-workshop)[Quantum Roadmap & Strategy](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-roadmap-strategy)\nRESOURCES\n[Resources](https://www.evolutionq.com/resources/resources)[Publications](https://www.evolutionq.com/resources/quantum-safe-publications)[FAQ](https://www.evolutionq.com/quantum-safe-cyber-security-faq)[Blog](https://www.evolutionq.com/blog)\nCOMPANY\n[About](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/about)[Careers](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/quantum-safe-careers)[Events](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/events)[News](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/news)[Partner Program](https://www.evolutionq.com/company/partner-program)[Contact](https://www.evolutionq.com/contact)\nSubscribe\nJoin our newsletter to stay up to date on features and releases.\n[Subscribe](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-safe-executive-workshop)\nBy subscribing you agree to our [Privacy Policy](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-safe-executive-workshop) and provide consent to receive updates from our company.\nThank you! Your submission has been received!\nOops! Something went wrong while submitting the form.\n\u00a9 2025 evolutionQ. All rights reserved.\n[Privacy Policy](https://www.evolutionq.com/legal/privacy-policy)[Disclosure Policy](https://www.evolutionq.com/legal/disclosure-policy)\n[Cookie Preferences](https://www.evolutionq.com/services/quantum-safe-executive-workshop)\n[![LinkedIn](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/64397268bacad8560a34f92a_linkedin.svg)](https://www.linkedin.com/company/evolutionq/)[![Twitter](https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63e68dd55d1e0e13004da649/6426526da75f4e45df4f421b_twitter.svg)](https://twitter.com/evolutionQinc)\nBasejump, BasejumpQDN and BasejumpSKI are trademarks of evolutionQ\n",
